  "prompt": "What are some English grammar tricks that I could learn in next 20 minutes?",
  "response": "Here are some helpful English grammar tricks you can learn quickly:\n\n1. Subject-Verb Agreement\n- Singular subjects take singular verbs\n- Plural subjects take plural verbs\nExample: \"He walks\" vs \"They walk\"\n\n2. Verb Tense Shortcut\n- Simple Present: Base verb (I walk)\n- Simple Past: Add -ed (I walked)\n- Present Continuous: Am/is/are + verb+ing (I am walking)\n\n3. Apostrophe Rules\n- For possession: Add 's (John's book)\n- For plural possession: Add s' (the dogs' toys)\n- For contractions: Replace missing letters (can't = cannot)\n\n4. Comma Usage\n- Use commas to separate items in a list\n- Use commas to separate independent clauses\n- Use commas after introductory phrases\n\n5. Commonly Confused Words\n- Their/There/They're\n- Your/You're\n- Its/It's\n- Affect/Effect\n\n6. Preposition Tricks\n- \"In\" for enclosed spaces\n- \"On\" for surfaces\n- \"At\" for specific points\n\n7. Adjective Order\nGenerally: Opinion-Size-Age-Shape-Color-Origin-Material-Purpose\nExample: \"A beautiful small old round blue Italian wooden table\"\n\nPractice these, and you'll quickly improve your grammar!",
